If light bends near dark matter, it is not being absorbed by dark matter. So dark matter has gravity but can't absorb light like other objects. Indirectly it is just an invisible nonempty space on space-time map. If light bends there, hence time exists inside dark matter. Therefore if we interact with dark matter, it would be similar to interacting another particle, like a black hole or other stars.(it would be dangerous, yet curious to know). Hence time near dark matter will work differently too! Such a cool connection 💯
